'''147''' ('''one hundred [and] forty-seven''') is the [[natural number]] following [[146 (number)|146]] and preceding [[148 (number)|148]].

The digits forming 147 also form the left-hand column of a normal decimal numeric keypad.
The binary form of 147 contains all the two-digit binary numbers (00, 01, 10 and 11).



