A '''uniquely inversible [[grammar]]''' is a [[formal grammar]] where no two distinct productions give the same [[result]].  This implies the specific production can be inferred from its results.

== Formal definition ==

<math>A \to \alpha \and B \to \beta \iff (A <> B \Rightarrow \alpha <> \beta)</math>

== Examples ==
;Uniquely inversibles

<math>A \to aA | bB </math>

<math>B \to b | a</math>

;Not uniquely inversibles {{Citation needed|date=July 2013}}

<math>A \to aA | bB</math>

<math>B \to bB | a</math>

<!--[[es:Gramáticas únicamente inversible]] broken link -->

[[Category:Formal languages]]
